habitat_description: The first report of this species is from an artesian well drilled in 1895 in the city of San Marcos in Hays County, Texas (Stejneger 1986; Lannoo 2005), now the campus of Southwest Texas State University. More recently, the species is known to occur in several wells, caves, and piping that intersect the San Marcos Pool of the Edwards Aquifer in the city of San Marcos at an elevation of about 188 meters (Green et al. 2013). The habitat of this species is completely aquatic and individuals are only found in caverns of the San Marcos Pool of the Edwards Aquifer (Lannoo 2005).
